They don't have to go into a variable at all if you don't want.

Most of the time I just pass them directly into the `parametrize` decorator, like so:

```python
@pytest.mark.parametrize('arg1, arg2', [
    (1, 2),
    (3, 4),
    (5, 6),
])
def test_func(arg1, arg2):
    assert func(arg1, arg2)

Resources is part of the response from the kernelspecs API (which I should probably note is different from local mode as we just see these as files). Example `GET` on `/api/kernelspecs`:

```
{
  "default": "python3",
  "kernelspecs": {
    "python3": {
      "name": "python3",
      "resources": {
        "logo-32x32":
          "/user/nteract-vdom-6m4yabcq/kernelspecs/python3/logo-32x32.png",
        "logo-64x64":
          "/user/nteract-vdom-6m4yabcq/kernelspecs/python3/logo-64x64.png"
      },
      "spec": {
        "display_name": "Python 3",
        "language": "python",
        "argv": [
          "python",
          "-m",
          "ipykernel_launcher",
          "-f",
          "{connection_file}"
        ],
        "env": {}
      }
    }
  }
}
```

